meanings: (음식을) eat, have, (formal) consume, (약 등을) take, (빨리) devour
You should not beat a dog while it is eating

vlive.english: What am I going to eat?
Are you going to eat it again?
Who wants a snack? ABNEW, hand!
What do you think when you eat mushrooms?
"When drinking beer, what do you have as a side dish?"

examples.english: the waifs and strays of our society

examples.korean: 우리는 두 나무 사이에 해먹을 쳤다[매달았다].
examples.english: We slung a hammock between two trees.

examples.english: You can still eat breakfast when you are slimming.

examples.english: The organization distributed food to the earthquake victims.

examples.korean: 개와 여우들이 먹을 것을 찾아 쓰레기통들을 뒤졌다.
examples.english: Dogs and foxes scavenged through the trash cans for something to eat.
